        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI (NIH, RH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint",
        "description": "The primary QoI — normalised index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100 L) — is the internationally recognised metric for pump-induced blood trauma and is specified in ISO 10993-4. The relative hemolysis index RH is derived directly from NIH and is the decision variable for the predicate comparison. No surrogate quantities are employed."
