      },
      "rationale": "Independent review of simulation setup reduces use-error risk beyond the minimum Gradation 1 requirement. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model-form uncertainty assessment for the power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) requires dedicated in-vitro scalar-transport validation experiments that fall outside the scope of this COU1 assessment. The hemolysis model coefficients are adopted directly from the peer-reviewed literature (Zhang et al. 2011, doi:10.1016/j.artmed.2011.01.003) and are considered fixed inputs for this analysis. A separate COU3 package (https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou3-model-form) addresses model-form credibility for the damage law. Scoping this factor out of COU1 is therefore justified and does not represent a gap in the overall credibility argument."
    },
