        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Single representative pump unit tested; unit-to-unit variability acknowledged",
        "description": "One FDA GCBP unit fabricated to nominal drawing dimensions used for all bench experiments. Unit-to-unit geometric variability is not characterised at MRL 2; this is acknowledged as a limitation addressed in the sensitivity analysis. Gradation 1 requires only that the test sample be documented and representative of the COU device."
      },
      "rationale": "Single representative unit is sufficient at MRL 2 / Gradation 1. Higher-gradation sample-variability study is deferred to a future MRL 3 assessment."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/equivalency-input-parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiment and the clinical COU is not assessed in this package because the validation test uses a blood analogue fluid (glycerol-saline) rather than human whole blood. The rheological differences between the analogue and whole blood are well-characterised in the literature (Brookshier and Tarbell 1993), and a separate fluid-equivalency study (https://uofa.net/morrison/study/fluid-equivalency-2023) has been commissioned to quantify the impact on hemolysis predictions. Until that study is complete, this factor is formally scoped out of COU1. The decision to accept the package despite this scoping is supported by the conservative nature of the analogue fluid (higher viscosity at low shear, tending to over-predict hemolysis) and the ±20% validation tolerance that partially absorbs fluid-property uncertainty."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-cpb-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The COU1 credibility assessment for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump CFD hemolysis model is accepted at Medium assurance / MRL 2. All 11 assessed factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. Two factors (Model form and Equivalency of input parameters) are formally scoped out with documented rationale referencing complementary assessments (COU3 and the fluid-equivalency study respectively). The primary QoI (NIH, RH) is directly clinically relevant, discretization error is below the 5% GCI threshold, and CFD predictions fall within ±20% of bench measurements at all five operating points. The scoping decisions are conservative and bounded: the hemolysis damage model coefficients are literature-validated, and the blood analogue is known to over-predict hemolysis, providing a safety margin. No factor achieves below its required level; hasOffsetRationale is therefore not required.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
